  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>eradication of barrett's esophagus and/or dysplasia</measure>
    <time_frame>3 to 6 months post treatment</time_frame>
    <description>Surveillance endoscopy with 4-quadrant biopsies every 1 cm from the gastric cardia, proceeding proximally at the length of the original BE lesion/s will be performed per standard clinical practice at 3 or 6 months post ablation. The presence of Barrett's Esophagus and degree of dysplasia will be confirmed by histopathologic diagnosis</description>
  </primary_outcome>
